Fifty years ago, on June 20, 1969, after humans first visited the moon, businesses are still trying to make a buck. Hundreds of millions of people were riveted when Apollo 11 astronauts landed on the moon. Naturally, marketers jumped at the chance to sell products. Americans prefer asteroid tracking over moon visit Americans prefer a space program focusing on potential asteroid impacts, scientific research into our cosmos and robotic space probes over human exploration of Mars or the moon, a new poll shows.